This paper deals with text-based entity classification, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the importance of separability in classification, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents a new model for capturing separability in hierarchical data, which could be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS).
